HEADWORD: Costmary
<hw>Cost"ma*ry</hw> <pr>(k?st"m?-r?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>costum</ets> an Oriental aromatic plant (Gr. <?/<?/<?/, cf. Ar.
<ets>kost</ets>, <ets>kust</ets>) + <ets>Maria</ets> Mary. Cf.
<er>Alecost</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A garden plant
(<spn>Chrysanthemum Balsamita</spn>) having a strong balsamic smell, and
nearly allied to tansy. It is used as a pot herb and salad plant and in
flavoring ale and beer. Called also
<altname>alecost</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

